<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFSteinberg1962">Steinberg, Alfred (1962). <i>The man from Missouri; the life and times of Harry S. Truman</i>. New York: Putnam. <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/466366" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/466366" rel="nofollow">466366</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+man+from+Missouri%3B+the+life+and+times+of+Harry+S.+Truman&amp;rft.aulast=Steinberg&amp;rft.aufirst=Alfred&amp;rft.au=Steinberg%2C+Alfred&amp;rft.date=1962&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Putnam&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/466366&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ku_Klux_Klan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTaylor1974">Taylor, Joe G. (1974). <i>Louisiana Reconstructed, 1863-1877</i>. Baton Rouge.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Louisiana+Reconstructed%2C+1863-1877&amp;rft.aulast=Taylor&amp;rft.aufirst=Joe+G.&amp;rft.au=Taylor%2C+Joe+G.&amp;rft.date=1974&amp;rft.place=Baton+Rouge&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ku_Klux_Klan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFThompson1982">Thompson, Jerry (1982). <i>My Life in the Klan</i>. New York: Putnam. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0399126953" class="internal">ISBN 0399126953</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=My+Life+in+the+Klan&amp;rft.aulast=Thompson&amp;rft.aufirst=Jerry&amp;rft.au=Thompson%2C+Jerry&amp;rft.date=1982&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Putnam&amp;rft.isbn=0399126953&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ku_Klux_Klan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTrelease1995">Trelease, Allen W. (1995). <i>White Terror: The Ku Klux Klan Conspiracy and Southern Reconstruction</i>. <a href="/wiki/Louisiana_State_University_Press" title="Louisiana State University Press">Louisiana State University Press</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=White+Terror%3A+The+Ku+Klux+Klan+Conspiracy+and+Southern+Reconstruction&amp;rft.aulast=Trelease&amp;rft.aufirst=Allen+W.&amp;rft.au=Trelease%2C+Allen+W.&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BLouisiana+State+University+Press%5D%5D&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ku_Klux_Klan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dd>First published in 1971 and based on massive research in primary sources, this is the most comprehensive treatment of the Klan and its relationship to post-Civil War Reconstruction. Includes narrative research on other night-riding groups. Details close link between Klan and late 19th century and early 20th century Democratic Party.</dd>
</dl>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWade1987">Wade, Wyn Craig (1987). <i>The Fiery Cross: The Ku Klux Klan in America</i>. New York: <a href="/wiki/Simon_and_Schuster" title="Simon and Schuster" class="mw-redirect">Simon and Schuster</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Fiery+Cross%3A+The+Ku+Klux+Klan+in+America&amp;rft.aulast=Wade&amp;rft.aufirst=Wyn+Craig&amp;rft.au=Wade%2C+Wyn+Craig&amp;rft.date=1987&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BSimon+and+Schuster%5D%5D&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ku_Klux_Klan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dd>An unsympathetic account of both Klans, with a dedication to "my Kentucky grandmother ... a fierce and steadfast Radical Republican from the wane of Reconstruction until her death nearly a century later".</dd>
</dl>
</div>
